ishes\", \"from\": 1018, \"to\": 1031}, {\"ngram\": \"cent\", \"from\": 1065, \"to\": 1069}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"People are going to meet here in France, with its culture, its heritage but also its gastronomy and so there are expectations,\\\" chief Paris 2024 organiser Tony Estanguet said.\", \"from\": 1083, \"to\": 1259, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1117, \"end\": 1123, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999838992154, \"rank\": 8.452585805918916e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1218, \"end\": 1228, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.811474318661101e-18, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1239, \"end\": 1253, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Tony Estanguet\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tony_Estanguet\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"People\", \"from\": 1084, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"its culture\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"its heritage\", \"from\": 1143, \"to\": 1155}, {\"ngram\": \"its gastronomy\", \"from\": 1165, \"to\": 1179}, {\"ngram\": \"expectations\", \"from\": 1197, \"to\": 1209}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Although many athletes would stick to their usual nutrition before competing, they will also be offered the chance to discover France's famed food, with several Michelin-starred chefs taken on as advisers.\", \"from\": 1261, \"to\": 1466, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1388, \"end\": 1394, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999999838992154, \"rank\": 8.452585805918916e-09, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1422, \"end\": 1438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Michelin-starred\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Michelin_Guide\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"many athletes\", \"from\": 1270, \"to\": 1283}, {\"ngram\": \"their usual nutrition\", \"from\": 1299, \"to\": 1320}, {\"ngram\": \"the chance\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1375}, {\"ngram\": \"advisers\", \"from\": 1457, \"to\": 1465}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We have allowed ourselves to put French gastronomy in pride of place so that curious athletes from around the world can try French culinary excellence,\\\" Estanguet added.\", \"from\": 1468, \"to\": 1638, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1502, \"end\": 1508, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8709136678544382, \"rank\": 0.14732665166346623, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1593, \"end\": 1599, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.8709136678544382, \"rank\": 0.14732665166346623, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"pride\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1528}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1537}, {\"ngram\": \"curious athletes\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1562}, {\"ngram\": \"the world\", \"from\": 1575, \"to\": 1584}, {\"ngram\": \"Estanguet\", \"from\": 1622, \"to\": 1631}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The giant warm-food buffets will not include French fries, however.\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1707, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1685, \"end\": 1697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_fries\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"French fries\", \"types\": [\"Q2095\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_fries\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_fries\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The giant warm-food buffets\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1667}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McDonalds, a long-time sponsor of the Olympics, had its own fast-food restaurant in the Olympic Village until the Rio Games in 2016, but athletes wanting a hit of junk food will have to look elsewhere in Paris.\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1919, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1797, \"end\": 1812, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0890121917267834e-18, \"text\": \"Olympic Village\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Village\"}, {\"begin\": 1913, \"end\": 1918, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1213289108297588e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"McDonalds\", \"from\": 1709, \"to\": 1718}, {\"ngram\": \"a long-time sponsor\", \"from\": 1720, \"to\": 1739}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympics\", \"from\": 1743, \"to\": 1755}, {\"ngram\": \"its own fast-food restaurant\", \"from\": 1761, \"to\": 1789}, {\"ngram\": \"the Rio Games\", \"from\": 1819, \"to\": 1832}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1846, \"to\": 1854}, {\"ngram\": \"a hit\", \"from\": 1863, \"to\": 1868}, {\"ngram\": \"junk food\", \"from\": 1872, \"to\": 1881}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"For technical reasons, we can not offer fries,\\\" said Estelle Lamotte, deputy director of village catering at food group Sodexo, explaining that deep-fat fryers were not allowed in the temporary kitchens at the site, which is usually used as a film studio.\", \"from\": 1921, \"to\": 2177, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1975, \"end\": 1982, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Estelle_Getty\", \"score\": 0.9998363133585273, \"rank\": 0.00016371338997831425, \"text\": \"Estelle\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Estelle_Getty\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Estelle_Getty\"}, {\"begin\": 2042, \"end\": 2048, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sodexo\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sodexo\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"technical reasons\", \"from\": 1926, \"to\": 1943}, {\"ngram\": \"fries\", \"from\": 1962, \"to\": 1967}, {\"ngram\": \"deputy director\", \"from\": 1992, \"to\": 2007}, {\"ngram\": \"village\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2018}, {\"ngram\": \"deep-fat fryers\", \"from\": 2066, \"to\": 2081}, {\"ngram\": \"the temporary kitchens\", \"from\": 2102, \"to\": 2124}, {\"ngram\": \"the site\", \"from\": 2128, \"to\": 2136}, {\"ngram\": \"a film studio\", \"from\": 2163, \"to\": 2176}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Gregoire Bechu, head of sustainable food at the Paris organising committee, stressed the quality of the \\\"delicious\\\" lentil dal recipe that has been developed for athletes.\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2350, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2227, \"end\": 2232, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1213289108297588e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Gregoire Bechu\", \"from\": 2179, \"to\": 2193}, {\"ngram\": \"head\", \"from\": 2195, \"to\": 2199}, {\"ngram\": \"sustainable food\", \"from\": 2203, \"to\": 2219}, {\"ngram\": \"the quality\", \"from\": 2264, \"to\": 2275}, {\"ngram\": \"the \\\"delicious\\\" lentil dal recipe\", \"from\": 2279, \"to\": 2312}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 2341, \"to\": 2349}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"One of the major commitments by Paris 2024 was offering vegetarian meals in order to halve the carbon footprint of each meal on average.\", \"from\": 2352, \"to\": 2489, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2385, \"end\": 2395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.811474318661101e-18, \"text\": \"Paris 2024\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2024_Summer_Olympics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the major commitments\", \"from\": 2360, \"to\": 2381}, {\"ngram\": \"vegetarian meals\", \"from\": 2409, \"to\": 2425}, {\"ngram\": \"order\", \"from\": 2429, \"to\": 2434}, {\"ngram\": \"the carbon footprint\", \"from\": 2444, \"to\": 2464}, {\"ngram\": \"each meal\", \"from\": 2468, \"to\": 2477}]}, {\"sentence\": \"We wanted vegetarian meals everywhere,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 2490, \"to\": 2538, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"vegetarian meals\", \"from\": 2500, \"to\": 2516}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At sports venues, 60 per cent of food offered to fans will be vegetarian and the temporary stadium hosting skateboarding, BMX and breakdancing at the Place de la Concorde in central Paris will be entirely meat-free.\", \"from\": 2540, \"to\": 2755, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2662, \"end\": 2665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"score\": 0.9999999853534974, \"rank\": 8.058154549259613e-09, \"text\": \"BMX\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/BMX\"}, {\"begin\": 2690, \"end\": 2710, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.015918965605098e-14, \"text\": \"Place de la Concorde\", \"types\": [\"Q34442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Place_de_la_Concorde\"}, {\"begin\": 2722, \"end\": 2727, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.1213289108297588e-17, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"sports venues\", \"from\": 2543, \"to\": 2556}, {\"ngram\": \"60 per cent\", \"from\": 2558, \"to\": 2569}, {\"ngram\": \"food\", \"from\": 2573, \"to\": 2577}, {\"ngram\": \"fans\", \"from\": 2589, \"to\": 2593}, {\"ngram\": \"the temporary stadium hosting skateboarding\", \"from\": 2617, \"to\": 2660}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In a further bid to lower carbon emissions, only two of the six restaurant areas at the village will be air-conditioned, with the rest in outdoor courtyards sheltered by fabric sun shades and ventilated with overhead fans.\", \"from\": 2757, \"to\": 2979, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a further bid\", \"from\": 2760, \"to\": 2773}, {\"ngram\": \"carbon emissions\", \"from\": 2783, \"to\": 2799}, {\"ngram\": \"the six restaurant areas\", \"from\": 2813, \"to\": 2837}, {\"ngram\": \"the village\", \"from\": 2841, \"to\": 2852}, {\"ngram\": \"the rest\", \"from\": 2883, \"to\": 2891}, {\"ngram\": \"outdoor courtyards\", \"from\": 2895, \"to\": 2913}, {\"ngram\": \"fabric sun\", \"from\": 2927, \"to\": 2937}, {\"ngram\": \"overhead fans\", \"from\": 2965, \"to\": 2978}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The June 25 test event, held under fierce sunshine and in 27 deg C heat, saw some people visibly sweating.\", \"from\": 2980, \"to\": 3086, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The June 25 test event\", \"from\": 2980, \"to\": 3002}, {\"ngram\": \"fi